1
00:00:00,834 --> 00:00:04,037
[rock music]

2
00:00:04,037 --> 00:00:08,542
♪

3
00:00:08,542 --> 00:00:10,110
[bell ringing]

4
00:00:10,110 --> 00:00:11,879
- Okay, class,
we're at the halfway point

5
00:00:11,879 --> 00:00:13,780
of our energy
reduction project.

6
00:00:13,780 --> 00:00:15,516
Let's see how you're doing.

7
00:00:15,516 --> 00:00:17,651
Great.
Very good.

8
00:00:17,651 --> 00:00:20,654
Ooh, very impressive, Clyde!

9
00:00:20,654 --> 00:00:22,022
- Thanks, Mrs. Johnson.

10
00:00:22,022 --> 00:00:24,157
Our house is solar powered,
so we don't burn

11
00:00:24,157 --> 00:00:25,392
any fossil fuels.

12
00:00:25,392 --> 00:00:26,460
- Wonderful.

13
00:00:26,460 --> 00:00:28,061
You're all doing a great job

14
00:00:28,061 --> 00:00:30,297
of reducing your eco-footprint
at home.

15
00:00:30,297 --> 00:00:31,798
And if you keep this up,

16
00:00:31,798 --> 00:00:35,135
we'll definitely win
the Save a Polar Bear Challenge

17
00:00:35,135 --> 00:00:38,238
and get this adorable little guy
named after us.

18
00:00:38,238 --> 00:00:40,607
all: Aww...

19
00:00:40,607 --> 00:00:44,444
- Oh, Lincoln, I see you haven't
made any progress.

20
00:00:44,444 --> 00:00:45,546
What does this say?

21
00:00:45,546 --> 00:00:47,714
"Have a heart,
do your part."

22
00:00:47,714 --> 00:00:50,184
Do you not care
about polar bears?

23
00:00:50,184 --> 00:00:51,885
- [muffled voice]
No, I don't!

24
00:00:51,885 --> 00:00:53,320
I don't hate polar bears.
They're awesome!

25
00:00:53,320 --> 00:00:54,621
- What's that?
You hate polar bears?

26
00:00:54,621 --> 00:00:56,290
You're a polar bear hater?

27
00:00:56,290 --> 00:00:58,392
- [muffled voice]
No, I love them--they're cool.

28
00:00:58,392 --> 00:01:00,060
[all jeering]

29
00:01:00,060 --> 00:01:03,564
- If you make us lose, Lincoln,
you'll be an outcast!

30
00:01:03,564 --> 00:01:06,900
- You might as well throw
your social life out the window.

31
00:01:06,900 --> 00:01:10,070
[all jeering]

32
00:01:11,805 --> 00:01:13,941
- How am I supposed
to reduce our energy use?

33
00:01:13,941 --> 00:01:15,475
I've got ten sisters!

34
00:01:15,475 --> 00:01:17,644
- I know, we'll just swoop in
from the left

35
00:01:17,644 --> 00:01:19,246
and annihilate them.

36
00:01:19,246 --> 00:01:21,481
- What?
Annihilate my sisters?

37
00:01:21,481 --> 00:01:22,549
- Huh? No.

38
00:01:22,549 --> 00:01:24,117
I was talking about our strategy

39
00:01:24,117 --> 00:01:26,553
for the "Swords and Cyborgs"
online tournament tomorrow.

40
00:01:26,553 --> 00:01:28,522
Preparation is key to victory.

41
00:01:28,522 --> 00:01:30,624
- Oh, yeah.
Don't worry, I'll be ready.

42
00:01:30,624 --> 00:01:32,826
But right now, I've got
bigger things to deal with.

43
00:01:32,826 --> 00:01:34,161
You heard our class:

44
00:01:34,161 --> 00:01:36,096
if I don't get
my eco-meter in the green,

45
00:01:36,096 --> 00:01:37,631
I'll be a social outcast.

46
00:01:37,631 --> 00:01:38,932
- I'll still hang out with you--

47
00:01:38,932 --> 00:01:39,933
in secret, of course,

48
00:01:39,933 --> 00:01:41,335
after dark.

49
00:01:41,335 --> 00:01:43,470
Speaking of which,
the sun's going down.

50
00:01:43,470 --> 00:01:45,639
I better get home
before the lights go out.

51
00:01:45,639 --> 00:01:48,475
[alarm blaring]

52
00:01:48,475 --> 00:01:51,411
- Maybe there's something wrong
with my eco-meter.

53
00:01:51,411 --> 00:01:54,014
[rumbling]

54
00:01:54,014 --> 00:01:55,382
Or not.
What can I do?

55
00:01:55,382 --> 00:01:57,251
In a family this big,

56
00:01:57,251 --> 00:02:00,787
our eco-footprint
is a size 18 triple wide.

57
00:02:00,787 --> 00:02:03,290
We use a lot of electricity...

58
00:02:03,290 --> 00:02:06,059
[stereo booming]

59
00:02:06,059 --> 00:02:09,196
- Bobby, you look so good
on all of my devices.

60
00:02:10,797 --> 00:02:13,100
[pie splatters, beeping]
- [laughing]

61
00:02:13,100 --> 00:02:15,068
- Fossil fuels...

62
00:02:21,241 --> 00:02:22,342
Water...

63
00:02:22,342 --> 00:02:23,477
- [humming]

64
00:02:27,080 --> 00:02:28,348
- Aerosols...

65
00:02:30,517 --> 00:02:32,286
- Non-biodegradables...

66
00:02:32,286 --> 00:02:35,088
And did I mention electricity?

67
00:02:37,224 --> 00:02:39,560
We've got to reduce
our eco-footprint.

68
00:02:39,560 --> 00:02:41,895
Hopefully I can get
my sisters on board.

69
00:02:41,895 --> 00:02:44,865
[all shouting at once]

70
00:02:44,865 --> 00:02:46,233
[pie splatters]

71
00:02:46,233 --> 00:02:49,870
- Or not.
Time to pull out the big guns.

72
00:02:49,870 --> 00:02:51,572
And if we don't all do our part,

73
00:02:51,572 --> 00:02:54,608
this adorable little guy
won't survive.

74
00:02:54,608 --> 00:02:57,444
[all crying]

75
00:02:57,444 --> 00:02:59,012
- But what can we do?

76
00:02:59,012 --> 00:03:00,914
- I'm glad you asked.

77
00:03:00,914 --> 00:03:02,282
You don't need
all these devices.

78
00:03:02,282 --> 00:03:03,717
- Yes, I do.

79
00:03:03,717 --> 00:03:06,453
Bobby and I like to admire
each other from multiple angles.

80
00:03:06,453 --> 00:03:09,523
- Hey, Lincoln.
"Hola" from France.

81
00:03:09,523 --> 00:03:12,659
- Who is that girl,
and why is she smiling at you?

82
00:03:12,659 --> 00:03:14,061
- Babe, that's the "Mona Lisa."

83
00:03:14,061 --> 00:03:16,496
- Instead of using
all of these,

84
00:03:16,496 --> 00:03:18,765
why don't you write
Bobby a letter?

85
00:03:18,765 --> 00:03:20,601
- Why don't I rip your little--

86
00:03:20,601 --> 00:03:22,369
- Polar bear.
- Aww...

87
00:03:22,369 --> 00:03:24,471
Okay, I'll write him a letter.

88
00:03:24,471 --> 00:03:27,541
And maybe I'll send one to
that little flirt Mona too.

89
00:03:27,541 --> 00:03:28,909
[water splashes]

90
00:03:28,909 --> 00:03:31,545
- But how will I keep
my reptiles warm?

91
00:03:31,545 --> 00:03:33,680
They're cold-blooded,
you know.

92
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:34,982
- But you're not.

93
00:03:39,920 --> 00:03:41,488
- [laughing]

94
00:03:41,488 --> 00:03:44,191
- Instead of powering your lab
with megawatts of electricity,

95
00:03:44,191 --> 00:03:48,095
why not use
a renewable resource?

96
00:03:48,095 --> 00:03:50,998
- [gasps]
Lincoln, this is genius.

97
00:03:50,998 --> 00:03:52,566
- Fresh energy coming at you.

98
00:03:52,566 --> 00:03:56,170
This one's got to be good
for at least 75 watts.

99
00:03:56,170 --> 00:03:57,504
[electricity buzzing]

100
00:03:58,739 --> 00:04:00,140
- [screaming]

101
00:04:00,140 --> 00:04:02,176
- Leni, instead of taking
multiple showers a day,

102
00:04:02,176 --> 00:04:04,711
how about using this refreshing
moist towelette?

103
00:04:04,711 --> 00:04:08,048
- And clog my pores?
No way!

104
00:04:08,048 --> 00:04:12,352
Aww...
okay.

105
00:04:12,352 --> 00:04:14,655
Do you mind?
I'm showering.

106
00:04:16,223 --> 00:04:17,958
- Luan, instead of wasting
all that energy

107
00:04:17,958 --> 00:04:19,593
making more pies,

108
00:04:19,593 --> 00:04:22,829
why not get some comedy out
of your leftover banana peels?

109
00:04:22,829 --> 00:04:25,766
- That old gag?
I don't think so.

110
00:04:25,766 --> 00:04:27,134
- Whoa!

111
00:04:27,134 --> 00:04:30,771
- Actually, I'm starting
to see the a-peel!

112
00:04:30,771 --> 00:04:32,372
[laughing]

113
00:04:32,372 --> 00:04:33,774
[alarm blaring]

114
00:04:33,774 --> 00:04:35,075
[watch dings]

115
00:04:35,075 --> 00:04:36,677
- We're getting there.

116
00:04:36,677 --> 00:04:39,680
[upbeat rock music]

117
00:04:39,680 --> 00:04:42,683
♪

118
00:04:42,683 --> 00:04:45,786
[electric guitar strumming]

119
00:04:45,786 --> 00:04:47,454
- [whistling]

120
00:04:47,454 --> 00:04:55,395
♪

121
00:05:00,167 --> 00:05:01,502
Almost there.

122
00:05:03,770 --> 00:05:05,105
[ding]

123
00:05:05,105 --> 00:05:06,640
We did it!

124
00:05:06,640 --> 00:05:08,575
[all cheering]

125
00:05:08,575 --> 00:05:11,144
- See what we can accomplish
when we all do our part?

126
00:05:11,144 --> 00:05:12,779
All we have to do
is keep the house in the green

127
00:05:12,779 --> 00:05:14,081
till the end of the week,

128
00:05:14,081 --> 00:05:16,083
and that polar bear
will be safe--

129
00:05:16,083 --> 00:05:18,318
and so will my social life.

130
00:05:18,318 --> 00:05:20,354
- Say it proud.
We're green and Loud!

131
00:05:20,354 --> 00:05:22,589
all: Say it proud--
we're green and Loud!

132
00:05:22,589 --> 00:05:24,858
Say it proud--
we're green and Loud!

133
00:05:24,858 --> 00:05:26,827
- Lincoln!
Come in, Lincoln!

134
00:05:26,827 --> 00:05:29,429
- Clyde, I'm not supposed to be
talking on this right now.

135
00:05:29,429 --> 00:05:31,265
We're reducing
our eco-footprint.

136
00:05:31,265 --> 00:05:32,666
- But it's tournament time.

137
00:05:32,666 --> 00:05:34,401
"Swords and Cyborgs"!

138
00:05:34,401 --> 00:05:36,603
- Oh, right.
Just let me go get my laptop.

139
00:05:36,603 --> 00:05:38,639
all: Yes, we care!
We'll save that bear!

140
00:05:38,639 --> 00:05:41,275
- What am I saying?
I can't use my laptop.

141
00:05:41,275 --> 00:05:42,910
We've finally gone green
in the house,

142
00:05:42,910 --> 00:05:44,311
and I can't mess it up.

143
00:05:44,311 --> 00:05:46,380
- Well, there's always
next year.

144
00:05:46,380 --> 00:05:48,282
- No, no, no.
I'll make it work.

145
00:05:48,282 --> 00:05:51,118
One laptop won't make
that big of a difference.

146
00:05:54,388 --> 00:05:57,591
[suspenseful music]

147
00:05:57,591 --> 00:06:02,162
♪

148
00:06:02,162 --> 00:06:03,530
[alarm blaring]
Whoops!

149
00:06:03,530 --> 00:06:05,399
I got to get us
back in the green.

150
00:06:07,935 --> 00:06:09,336
- Hey, what the--

151
00:06:09,336 --> 00:06:12,139
- Remember this guy?
- Yes, we saved him.

152
00:06:12,139 --> 00:06:13,707
- Well, he's got siblings too.

153
00:06:13,707 --> 00:06:16,410
Do you hate siblings?
Are you sibling haters?

154
00:06:16,410 --> 00:06:18,212
- Well, I'm starting to.

155
00:06:21,315 --> 00:06:24,551
- Hey, guys,
our neighborhood's on TV!

156
00:06:26,053 --> 00:06:27,421
- Hey, Lincoln.
- Argh!

157
00:06:27,421 --> 00:06:29,056
Clyde, what are you
doing here?

158
00:06:29,056 --> 00:06:30,490
- The sun went behind a cloud.

159
00:06:30,490 --> 00:06:32,192
My solar house lost power.

160
00:06:32,192 --> 00:06:33,861
Is it okay if I play here?

161
00:06:33,861 --> 00:06:35,362
[alarm blaring]

162
00:06:35,362 --> 00:06:37,464
- I just got us back
into the green.

163
00:06:37,464 --> 00:06:40,367
- Sorry, Lincoln, I didn't mean
to cause a problem.

164
00:06:40,367 --> 00:06:42,436
- No, no, Clyde.
Not a problem.

165
00:06:42,436 --> 00:06:44,805
I'll just go make an adjustment.

166
00:06:44,805 --> 00:06:46,073
[knocking]

167
00:06:46,073 --> 00:06:47,474
If it's yellow, let it mellow!

168
00:06:47,474 --> 00:06:49,710
- Um, what if it's not?

169
00:06:49,710 --> 00:06:52,746
- If it's brown,
keep it around.

170
00:06:52,746 --> 00:06:53,780
- Ew!

171
00:06:53,780 --> 00:06:55,782
Aww...

172
00:06:55,782 --> 00:06:59,319
- Hey, guys, think we could
turn off the AC?

173
00:06:59,319 --> 00:07:01,121
- But we're trying to stay cool.

174
00:07:01,121 --> 00:07:03,023
- You know who else
wants to stay cool?

175
00:07:03,023 --> 00:07:04,157
This guy.

176
00:07:04,157 --> 00:07:06,627
- Aww...

177
00:07:06,627 --> 00:07:09,162
[AC crashing]

178
00:07:09,162 --> 00:07:12,432
- Look, I'm your number one fan!
[laughing]

179
00:07:12,432 --> 00:07:14,601
- [laughing]
Good one, honey.

180
00:07:14,601 --> 00:07:16,236
Well, I'm off.

181
00:07:16,236 --> 00:07:18,438
- Hey, Dad, instead of taking
the car,

182
00:07:18,438 --> 00:07:20,440
why not enjoy
a little fresh air?

183
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:22,176
- I'm picking up your mom
from the airport.

184
00:07:22,176 --> 00:07:24,811
- Then you'll need this.

185
00:07:24,811 --> 00:07:27,047
[alarm dinging]

186
00:07:27,047 --> 00:07:28,482
What are you guys doing here?

187
00:07:28,482 --> 00:07:30,450
- Can't play "Sword and Cyborgs"
at our houses.

188
00:07:30,450 --> 00:07:31,952
We're in the green zone.

189
00:07:31,952 --> 00:07:33,187
- Well, so am I--

190
00:07:33,187 --> 00:07:35,088
or I was.

191
00:07:35,088 --> 00:07:37,157
- Well, if it's a problem,
we can go.

192
00:07:37,157 --> 00:07:40,093
- No, no, no.
I'll make an adjustment.

193
00:07:40,093 --> 00:07:43,096
[grunting]

194
00:07:46,900 --> 00:07:48,068
- Ahh.

195
00:07:48,068 --> 00:07:50,838
[crashing, groaning]

196
00:07:50,838 --> 00:07:52,239
- Sweet!
Snacks!

197
00:07:52,239 --> 00:07:53,941
Let's put them by
the air conditioner

198
00:07:53,941 --> 00:07:55,309
we found outside.

199
00:07:55,309 --> 00:07:56,910
[alarm blaring]

200
00:07:56,910 --> 00:08:00,647
But if it's not cool, Lincoln,
I mean, just say the word.

201
00:08:00,647 --> 00:08:03,016
- No, no.
Adjustment.

202
00:08:03,016 --> 00:08:06,019
[upbeat rock music]

203
00:08:06,019 --> 00:08:13,627
♪

204
00:08:13,627 --> 00:08:16,029
Can't run the washer
if there's nothing to wash.

205
00:08:16,029 --> 00:08:24,805
♪

206
00:08:24,805 --> 00:08:28,775
What else is there?

207
00:08:28,775 --> 00:08:30,210
[dinging]

208
00:08:30,210 --> 00:08:32,946
- We are in the green.
Let's do this!

209
00:08:32,946 --> 00:08:36,917
- Whew, what stinks?

210
00:08:36,917 --> 00:08:38,585
- Game over, Lincoln!

211
00:08:38,585 --> 00:08:40,654
- It's not what it looks like!

212
00:08:40,654 --> 00:08:42,523
- We're up there making
all these sacrifices,

213
00:08:42,523 --> 00:08:44,758
and you're down here playing
some stupid computer game?

214
00:08:44,758 --> 00:08:47,694
- Okay, so maybe it is
what it looks like.

215
00:08:47,694 --> 00:08:50,931
- If you don't want to
give anything up, why should we?

216
00:08:50,931 --> 00:08:53,200
- But--but--
polar bear?

217
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:54,868
- Aww--wait a minute.

218
00:08:54,868 --> 00:08:56,637
You can't use that
on us anymore.

219
00:08:56,637 --> 00:09:00,073
- Come on, girls.
Let's go get our stuff back.

220
00:09:00,073 --> 00:09:03,844
- And a refill.

221
00:09:03,844 --> 00:09:06,213
- Well, I guess you're
going back into the red.

222
00:09:06,213 --> 00:09:08,782
- Which means you're gonna lose
the polar bear challenge

223
00:09:08,782 --> 00:09:10,017
for our class.

224
00:09:10,017 --> 00:09:12,019
- Which means we can't
be seen with you.

225
00:09:12,019 --> 00:09:15,722
- Which means your social life
is out the window.

226
00:09:15,722 --> 00:09:17,858
- Guys, wait!
Come back!

227
00:09:17,858 --> 00:09:19,393
I can make adjustments.

228
00:09:19,393 --> 00:09:22,095
I blew it.
- Don't worry, Lincoln.

229
00:09:22,095 --> 00:09:25,265
I'll still hang out with you--
in secret, of course.

230
00:09:25,265 --> 00:09:26,800
- It's not about that,
Clyde.

231
00:09:26,800 --> 00:09:28,769
I don't care
if the class hates me.

232
00:09:28,769 --> 00:09:30,871
What I should have cared about
all along is--

233
00:09:30,871 --> 00:09:31,872
this guy.

234
00:09:31,872 --> 00:09:33,140
- Aww...

235
00:09:33,140 --> 00:09:35,576
- Exactly.
Our class has done their part.

236
00:09:35,576 --> 00:09:37,377
My sisters have done theirs.

237
00:09:37,377 --> 00:09:39,413
Now it's time for me
to do mine.

238
00:09:41,248 --> 00:09:44,251
[stereo blasting rock music]

239
00:09:44,251 --> 00:09:45,452
♪

240
00:09:45,452 --> 00:09:48,956
[pie splatters, beeping]
- [laughing]

241
00:09:48,956 --> 00:09:51,058
- [humming]

242
00:09:51,058 --> 00:09:52,159
[electricity buzzing]

243
00:09:52,159 --> 00:09:54,761
- [laughing]

244
00:09:54,761 --> 00:09:56,864
- [giggling]
Oh, Bobby.

245
00:09:56,864 --> 00:09:59,166
You got me a present?
I can't wait to see it.

246
00:09:59,166 --> 00:10:04,037
- [panting]

247
00:10:04,037 --> 00:10:05,973
- Lincoln, pedal faster!

248
00:10:05,973 --> 00:10:09,510
I'm downloading a pic
from Bobby.

249
00:10:09,510 --> 00:10:11,445
- Amazing work, class.

250
00:10:11,445 --> 00:10:13,914
We won the polar bear challenge!

251
00:10:13,914 --> 00:10:17,050
And I took the liberty
of naming him...

252
00:10:17,050 --> 00:10:19,319
Mrs. Johnson!

253
00:10:19,319 --> 00:10:20,988
all: Mrs. Johnson?
[muttering]

254
00:10:20,988 --> 00:10:23,724
- Let's all give Lincoln
a round of applause

255
00:10:23,724 --> 00:10:27,528
for stepping up his green game
and doing his part.

256
00:10:27,528 --> 00:10:29,596
[all cheering]

257
00:10:29,596 --> 00:10:33,200
- Well, I saved the polar bear,
and I'm not an outcast.

258
00:10:33,200 --> 00:10:35,636
Although,
